Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt and @pepper, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pick the @Mint{1}(leaves picked from stalks and roughly chopped) leaves from their stalks, then roughly chop (discard the stalks) and pop into a small #bowl. Add the @Greek Style Natural Yoghurt{150%g}, season with @salt and @pepper, then set aside.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Onion{1}. Trim the @Carrot{1}, then coarsely grate (no need to peel).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the onion and carrot, season with @salt and @pepper, then stir-fry until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

In the meantime, halve the @Baby Plum Tomatoes{125%g} and pop them into a medium #bowl. Drizzle over a little oil and season with @salt and @pepper. Set aside.

When the carrot and onion have softened, transfer to a large #bowl - keep the pan, you'll use it again.

Add the @Korma Curry Paste{50%g}, @Plain Flour{40%g}, @Salt{¼%tsp} and @Egg{1} (see pantry for all amounts) to the large bowl. Season with @salt and @pepper, then mix together well.

> Lift out some of the mixture with a spoon - if it's too wet and doesn't hold its shape, add a little more flour.

Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with enough oil to coat the bottom.

Once the oil is hot, place heaped tablespoons of the fritter mixture (in batches) into the pan. Flatten slightly with the back of your #spoon, then fry until golden and cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes} each side.

> Don't flip them too early, they need time to set.

Once cooked, transfer to a #plate lined with #kitchen paper. Keep cooking in batches until all the mixture is used up - you should get 3-4 fritters per person.

> Add extra oil in between batches if needed.

While the last batch of fritters are frying, halve the @Burger Buns{2} and pop them into the #oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once warmed, transfer to your plates. Spread as much of the mint yoghurt as you'd like over the bun bases.

Once the fritters are ready, stack them up on the bun bases and top with a handful of @Wild Rocket{40%g}. Spread the @Mango Chutney{40%g} onto the bun lids, then sandwich together.

Add the remaining rocket to the bowl of tomatoes. Toss together to coat.

Serve your bhaji fritter burgers with the chips and salad alongside. Serve any remaining mint yoghurt on the side for dipping.

Enjoy!